text: Yvonne Strahovski Net Worth and salary: Yvonne Strahovski is an Australian actress who has a net worth of $12 million. Yvonne Strahovski earned her net worth entertaining audiences with her acting performances on the screen and made for TV movies. She was born Yvonne Jaqueline Strzechowski on July 30, 1982, in Campbelltown, a suburb of Sydney. She first became famous for her role as Agent Sarah Walker on the NBC comedy series Chuck (2007–2012). Even though she had already been popular in her native Australia, the action-packed series unveiled Strahovski's natural talents and appeal in front of American audience. As talented as beautiful, Strzechowski mesmerized both men and women viewers, the first being mainly drawn by her sleek and sexy physique, while the latter by her comedic and dramatic flair. This led her to appear in other Hollywood productions like the suspense thriller Killer Elite (2011), where she played the sultry love interest of Jason Statham. Her other notable film projects include the 2012 comedy The Guilt Trip, 2014's horror epic I, Frankenstein and 2016's All I see Is You. She was the voice and model of Miranda Lawson in the Mass Effect video game trilogy. She appeared in season 7 and 8 of the TV series Dexter. In 2014, she appeared in 12 episodes of the rebooted 24. In 2015, she appeared in 10 episodes of The Astronaut Wives Club. Starting in 2017, Yvonne Strahovski began appearing in the critically acclaimed Hulu series The Handmaid's Tale. In 2017, she married her partner of six years Tim Loden. In May 2018 they announced they were expecting their first child together.
